sec.p:
The fiber length parameters included in our models are:


Mean Length by Weight (MLw);

CV of Length by Weight (Lw_CV);

UQL by Weight (UQLw);

Mean Length by Number (MLn);

CV of Length by Number (Ln_CV);

UQL by Number (UQLn);

UHML;

Uniformity Index (UI). In addition to the above parameters, short fiber parametrs were also included in the models. They are:

SFCn and 10) SFCw, which is the SFC defined as the percentage of fibers shorter than ½ inch by number and by weight;12

SFC16w, which is the SFC defined as the percentage of fibers shorter than 16 mm by weight;13

Lower Half Mean Length (LHML), defined as the ML (by number) of the short half of the fibers by weight;14

Relative SFC (Rel_SFCw), defined as the percentage of fibers by weight shorter than half of the UHML;15

Floating Fiber Proportion (FFP) defined as FFP = (S2.5/MLn − 0.975) × 100, where S2.5 is the 2.5% span length;16

Floating Fiber Index (FFI) is defined as FFI = (UQLw/MLw − 1) × 100.17
